Reasoning: The paper discusses a platform for teaching distributed software development in project courses, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The platform also involves the use of a development environment, which could be categorized under computer engineering (cs.CE). The challenges and risks associated with distributed software development could also be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper mentions the use of routines and processes for conducting the courses, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
